    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-10-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-10-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="809"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d809">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 European War/10–1044</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        British Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Halifax</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <p>The Secretary of State presents his compliments to His Excellency the British
                    Ambassador and has the honor to refer to the Embassy’s note No. 601, Reference:
                    3136/5/44, dated September 30, 1944, concerning the mistreatment of Allied
                    parachutists who fall into German hands.</p>
                <p>There is transmitted herewith for the Embassy’s information a copy of the
                    Department’s telegram of today’s date to the American Legation at Bern<note
                        n="51" xml:id="d809fn51">Telegram 3604, October 23, <hi rend="italic"
                            >supra.</hi>
                    </note> which sets forth the protest which the Swiss Government is being
                    requested to deliver to the German Government in this connection.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-24">October 24,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
